  fishType: Tilapia
  displayName: Tilapia
  difficulty: 1
  educationalInfo: Tilapia is a popular freshwater fish. When deboning, start by
    making a careful cut along the spine with a knife, then use tweezers to remove
    the pin bones carefully. The pin bones along the sides must be removed for a
    clean fillet.
  description: A freshwater fish perfect for beginners. Has a simple bone structure
    with clearly visible ribs.
  timeLimitSeconds: 90
  spineBoneCount: 1
  ribBoneCount: 3
  pinBoneCount: 2
  habitat: Freshwater lakes and rivers
  cookingTips: Tilapia is versatile and can be grilled, fried, or baked. Make sure
    all bones are removed for safe eating.
